Iceland has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Iceland, see Return to the UK
Travel restrictions
From 24 April everyone arriving in Iceland from abroad is required to self-isolate for 14 days upon arrival. You can find further information from the Icelandic authorities at Covid.is (available in English).
Local measures
Wide ranging restrictions are in place.
These include, but are not limited to, self-isolation on arrival, social distancing, bans on gatherings over certain numbers, closure of bars, nightclubs, swimming pools and gyms.
Detailed and up to date information on the full range of restrictions can be found at Covid.is (available in English).
You should also regularly monitor Government announcements for any rapid changes at www.government.is/.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
You can find more information about cases in Iceland on the Covid.is website.
